      public void close()
      Description copied from interface: RowSet
      Normally a RowSet is processed until complete which implicitly closes any underlying resources. This "close" operation exists to explicitly end use of the RowSet in cases where it does happen. There is no need to close RowSets normally - it is the QueryExec that should be closed.
